sentences: Aki Takase (高瀬 アキ) (born January 26, 1948) is a Japanese jazz pianist and composer.
Starting in 1978, Takase began performing and recording in the US.
Her first European appearance was in 1981 at the Berlin Jazz Festival in Germany.

In various projects, Takase has dealt with the respective oeuvres of numerous famous jazz musicians, including the works of Duke Ellington (1990), Thelonious Monk (1994), Eric Dolphy (1998), W.C. Handy (2002), Fats Waller (2004), and Ornette Coleman (2006).
